						<summary>

						<p>Slab in the ruined Gavi-Siddēśvara temple on the bank of the Hirehaḷḷa about a mile to the south of the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Mahādēva 1186 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This very badly damaged record seems to have registered a grant mentions to a basadi of which details are lost. It refers to Kūṇḍi-3000 and to <hi rend="italic">piriya agrahāra</hi> Kabbūr, Kallarasa, an officer probably in charge of a division is also mentioned.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the (regnal) year 7, Prabha(va), Bhādrapada, śu. 3 Monday. The date is wrong. Regnal year 7 falls in the cyclic year Viśvāvasu. The cyclic year Prabhava mentioned here do not tally. It may be a mistake for Parābhava which occured in Śaka 1108. Then the given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> can be equated with 1186 A.D., August 19, Tuesday. In the cyclic year Viśvāvasu the given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> occured on 1185 A.D., July 31, Wednesday.</p>						

						</summary>
